article.headline: Cal State Northridge 102, Eastern Washington 98
article.story: LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Calvin Chitwood scored a career-high 30 points and grabbed a key rebound late in the game Sunday, leading Cal State Northridge to a 102-98 victory over Eastern Washington. Chitwood shot 8-of-12 from the floor and converted all 12 of his foul shots. Three of his baskets came on follow dunks off missed shots by teammates. Chitwood made two free throws with 1:14 remaining to give Northridge (5-3) a 97-94 lead. The most important of his nine rebounds came 22 seconds later when he grabbed a missed 3-pointer by Eastern Washington's Rodney Stuckey, who scored 32 points. Jonathan Heard came off the bench to score 19 points and Jayme Miller and Rob Haynes scored 13 each for the Matadors. Among those in attendance were representatives from six NBA teams watching Stuckey, the reigning Big Sky Conference freshman of the year. In addition to his 32 points, Stuckey had six rebounds, seven assists and four steals. Stuckey, who scored 22 of his points in the first half, shot 9-of-17 from the floor and 10-of-12 from the foul line. Paul Butorac matched his career high with 20 points and Omar Krayem added 10 for the Eagles (4-4).
